As his classmates celebrate their middle school graduation, troubled Mirai is mired in darkness. But his battle is just beginning when he receives some salvation from above in the form of an angel. Now Mirai is pitted against 12 other chosen humans in a battle in which the winner becomes the next god of the world. Mirai has an angel in his corner, but he may need to become a devil to survive.
(Source: Viz Media)
Kimetsu no Yaiba: Shiawase no Hana

The first light novel written by Aya Yajima for Kimetsu no Yaiba containing five chapters, as well as an afterword. 1. Shiawase no Hana Takes place after the Drum House arc and centers around Tanjiro, Zenitsu, and Inosuke bonding while attending a village wedding. 2. Dare ga Tame ni Takes place after the Natagumo Mountain arc during a "date" between Zenitsu and Nezuko. Zenitsu begins to reminisce about his past encounter with a woman named Sayuri. 3. Uranai Sd Tenmatsuki Takes place after the Infinity Train arc. Shinobu attempts to cheer the Kamaboko trio up by sending them to buy sweets. On the way back to the Butterfly Mansion, the trio encounter a fortune teller. 4. Aoi to Kanao Shinobu sends Kanao to accompany Aoi on a trip to the apothecary. 5. Chkikan Kimetsu Gakuen Monokatari Modern-day school alternate universe where Zenitsu has had enough of the Morals Committee and begs his friends to help him quit the club. A seemingly easy task becomes complicated when all of the teachers turn out to be unreliable.
